1
00:00:01,165 --> 00:00:06,165
SPECTRA. Raw I/Q in, threat picture out.

2
00:00:06,167 --> 00:00:11,167
Marine FOB Spectrum Awareness — what is in my bubble, is any of it not ours?

3
00:00:11,169 --> 00:00:16,169
Six synthetic 1-second I/Q captures. NIST SigMF schema.

4
00:00:16,298 --> 00:00:21,298
STFT renders the spectrogram. SigMF header on the right.

5
00:00:21,299 --> 00:00:26,299
Multimodal model ingests the spectrogram plus the SigMF header.

6
00:00:21,335 --> 00:00:27,335
Strict JSON: modulation, protocol, anomaly flag, confidence.

7
00:00:32,337 --> 00:00:37,337
Hero model drafts a SIPR-format Spectrum Awareness Brief.

8
00:00:37,345 --> 00:00:43,345
BLUF, header, top emitters, anomalies, recommended actions.

9
00:00:43,346 --> 00:00:48,346
Three clicks: pick a capture, classify, draft the brief.

10
00:00:48,396 --> 00:00:53,396
Unauthorized-band emitter. Cached brief loads instantly.

11
00:00:53,402 --> 00:00:59,402
Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL — same code, now on the Inference Mesh.

12
00:00:59,403 --> 00:01:04,403
IL5 / IL6 ready. ReBAC. Air-gapped. Zero data movement.

13
00:01:04,405 --> 00:01:09,405
SPECTRA. Built on the Kamiwaza Stack. Powered by Kamiwaza.
